The McDonald's at Randolph and Dearborn is solid, but very busy. This means very quick service. Be prepared to moving quickly through the line at peak hours. This location is nicely spacious, and it's important to realize that there's dining space upstairs. Use the stairs to access the upper level to take advantage of the additional seating there. (Sometimes the volume of people in this site is a challenge, so you might find yourself knee-to-knee with other guests. As much as this location of McDonald's has additional seating, sometimes other guests have a lot of packages, coats, and other belongings with them.) In terms of service it is very brisk and quite accurate. The staff is professional and responds well to special requests. The food is the same as other McDonald's, but the volume at this one seems make the food seem fresher. It hardly ever sits on the counter for more than a few seconds before you get your order. Traffic inside the restaurant bears some attention. It's easy to walk into other customers, so keep your head up and make eye contact.  It will all work at this busy location, which is conveniently near the Oriental Theater, Daley Plaza, and Macy's. It's also neatly adjacent the stop for northbound 36 and 22 bus lines, and across the street from the bike lane that runs on much of Dearborn in the Loop.
